success.question_text: At what time will it finish?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Time

stimulus_2.text: A movie commences at twenty-five to eleven. It runs for 95 minutes.

review_3.column_1_text:
95 minutes = 1 hour and 35 minutes

The movie begins 25 minutes before 11 o’clock.

One hour later is 25 minutes before 12 o’clock.

Thirty-five minutes after that is 10 minutes past 12 o’clock.

The movie will finish at 12:10.

 

Tip

Be very careful when adding times. They are not decimals.

success.question_text: What is the length of the key?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Length

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Make sure that you can accurately measure lengths.

success.question_text: The area of the front of a business-sized envelope would be closest to
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Area

success.question_text:
Of the 250 students enrolled in a course 150 are male.

What is the ratio of male to female students in the course?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Ratio and Rates

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Order is very important in a ratio. The ratio of male to female students, for example, is different to the ratio of female to male students.

success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Volume and Capacity

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

The height of any solid is always perpendicular (at right-angles) to the base.

success.question_text:
David used 12 litres of fuel when he travelled 150 km.

What is his fuel consumption as a rate in litres per 100 km?

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Fuel consumption is usually given as a number of litres per 100 km. Make sure you can understand that type of rate.

success.question_text: What is the value of x?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Pythagoras Theorem

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

Pythagoras’ theorem says that in any right-angled triangle the square on the hypotenuse is equal to the sum of the squares on the other two sides.

success.question_text: What is the total area of all the faces of this prism?

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

The surface area of a solid is the sum of the areas of all the faces.

success.question_text:
A truck is loaded with cargo weighing 12.37 tonnes. 780 kilograms are added at the first stop and at the second stop 1.61 tonnes are removed.

Which is closest to the weight of the load after the second stop?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Mass

success.question_text:
Jodi has a packet of 24 red and blue balloons. The ratio of red to blue balloons is 3:5. Jodi blows up two of each colour.

What is the ratio of red to blue balloons remaining in the packet?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Ratio and Rates

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

Order is very important in a ratio. The ratio of red balloons to blue balloons, for example, is different to the ratio of blue balloons to red balloons.

success.question_text:
A rectangle is three times as long as it is wide.

Which statement will correctly complete the sentence: ‘The perimeter is …’?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Perimeter

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

The perimeter is the distance around the whole shape. For a rectangle with length l and breadth b the perimeter is given by P = 2l + 2b.

success.question_text:
A regular hexagon of side length 8 cm is made from wire.

If the wire is straightened and then bent to form a square, what is the area of the square?

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

Think carefully and work logically through any problem. Drawing a diagram might help.

success.question_text: In which diagram is the perpendicular height of the trapezium 12 cm?

review_5.column_1_text:
Tip

A trapezium is a quadrilateral with one pair of opposite sides parallel. Perpendicular means at right angles. The perpendicular height of a trapezium is the distance between the two parallel sides.

success.question_text: How else could this capacity be described?

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

Always make sure that the same units are used in calculations. For example, in this question because the area was measured in square metres, the depth needed to be in metres, not centimetres.

success.question_text:
A car travels x km in y hours at z km/h.

Which is correct?

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Substitute numbers into expressions if you are unsure what should be done. For example, in this question if z = 60 and y = 2, the car obviously travels 120 km in 2 hours so x = 120. Now substitute into each option to see which one works.
